
(1) Homogenized Energy Polarization Model

The main file for the homogenized energy polarization model
developed in Section 2.6 is

  polarization_model_demo.m

which provides the capability for running the model
with or without thermal activation using general densities
or a priori density choices.  The model with thermal activation
is much slower than that without thermal activation.

Required Data Files:
  params_pzt_gen_demo.dat
  params_pzt_log_demo.dat
  params_pzt_log_freq_demo.dat

Required Functions:
  polar_func.m
  gauss_weights.m
  gauss_weights.m 

Relevant Sections
  Section 2.6


(2) Inverse Polarization Model

The main file for the inverse polarization model detailed
in Section 2.6.7 is

  inverse_polar_model_demo.m

Required Data Files:
  params_pzt_gen_demo.dat
  params_pzt_log_demo.dat
  params_pzt_log_freq_demo.dat

Required Functions:
  inverse_polar_func.m
  gauss_weights.m
  gauss_weights.m

Relevant Sections
  Section 2.6.7


